{
  "stem": "25598.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So it was a resort town where a lot of people used to come to spend their vacations, wintertime and summertime alike-- more so, summertime, but wintertime too because it was a ski resort.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in the summer a lot of people would come from Bucharest, which is the capital of Romania, or all kinds of other places where it got much hotter than it was in the mountains.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we made a lot of friends.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, my parents made a lot of friends with all these people.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we made a lot of connections, which were helpful to us when we were deported-- through these tourists that used to come, mostly Jewish people, also.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Most of the Jewish people in town were merchants.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were also clerks, and there was a big wood mill where a lot of people worked.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was, of course, a shochet and rabbis, and the barber, and the baker, and the tailor, and, and the matchmaker, and the whole structure, the whole richness of, of Jewish life in Romania, which was very rich because Romania was-- had the third-largest Jewish community in Europe, after Poland and Russia.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Or I believe it was Russia and Poland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I believe in Russia, there were more.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And Jewish life was very vibrant and very energetic.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there were a lot of Zionist organizations for youth and for adults.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And everybody--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I did.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But before the war, I was only 10 years old.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I belonged to an organization called Hanoar Hatzioni, which was sort of a middle-- well, we gathered, and we danced, and whatever.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, at least once a week, at least.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
